Subject: [PATCH 4.19 63/69] xen/blkfront: dont take local copy of a request from the ring page
Date:   Mon, 29 Nov 2021 19:18:45 +0100
Message-Id: <20211129181705.694898315@linuxfoundation.org>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.34.1
In-Reply-To: <20211129181703.670197996@linuxfoundation.org>
References: <20211129181703.670197996@linuxfoundation.org>
User-Agent: quilt/0.66
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <stable.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: stable@vger.kernel.org

From: Juergen Gross <jgross@suse.com>

commit 8f5a695d99000fc3aa73934d7ced33cfc64dcdab upstream.

In order to avoid a malicious backend being able to influence the local
copy of a request build the request locally first and then copy it to
the ring page instead of doing it the other way round as today.

